{
  "id": "ia-a1-u2",
  "title": "To Be & Pronouns",
  "level": "A1",
  "summary": "The whole verb system's best surprise: nothing conjugates.",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "l1",
      "title": "Io es, tu es",
      "teach": [
        {
          "target": "io",
          "roman": "io",
          "english": "I",
          "ipa": "ˈiʲo",
          "audio": "audio/io.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "tu",
          "roman": "tu",
          "english": "you",
          "ipa": "tˈu",
          "audio": "audio/tu.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "ille / illa",
          "roman": "ille illa",
          "english": "he / she",
          "ipa": "ˈile ˈila",
          "audio": "audio/ille-illa.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "es",
          "roman": "es",
          "english": "am / is / are",
          "note": "One form for every person. Io es, tu es, illa es — that's it.",
          "ipa": "ˈes",
          "audio": "audio/es.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Io es felice.",
          "roman": "io es felice",
          "english": "I am happy.",
          "ipa": "ˈiʲo es felˈitse",
          "audio": "audio/io-es-felice.wav"
        }
      ],
      "grammar": {
        "title": "No conjugation. Ever.",
        "body": "In Interlingua a verb has **one present form for all persons**:\n| io es | I am |\n| tu es | you are |\n| ille/illa es | he/she is |\n| nos es | we are |\nCompare Spanish (soy/eres/es/somos/sois/son) — Interlingua deleted the whole table. What you save in memorization you can spend on vocabulary."
      },
      "exercises": [
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "prompt": "\"Illa es felice\" means…",
          "choices": [
            "She is happy",
            "He is happy",
            "I am happy",
            "You are happy"
          ],
          "answer": 0,
          "tts": "illa es felice"
        },
        {
          "type": "type",
          "prompt": "Translate: \"I am\"",
          "answer": "io es",
          "tts": "io es"
        },
        {
          "type": "listen",
          "ttsText": "tu es",
          "prompt": "Which did you hear?",
          "choices": [
            "tu es",
            "io es",
            "ille es"
          ],
          "answer": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "prompt": "How does \"es\" change with different subjects?",
          "choices": [
            "It never changes",
            "It adds -s for you",
            "It changes for each person",
            "It has 6 forms"
          ],
          "answer": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "match",
          "prompt": "Match the pronouns",
          "pairs": [
            [
              "io",
              "I"
            ],
            [
              "tu",
              "you"
            ],
            [
              "ille",
              "he"
            ],
            [
              "illa",
              "she"
            ]
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "l2",
      "title": "We, you all, they — and to have",
      "teach": [
        {
          "target": "nos",
          "roman": "nos",
          "english": "we",
          "ipa": "nˈos",
          "audio": "audio/nos.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "vos",
          "roman": "vos",
          "english": "you (plural/formal)",
          "ipa": "vˈos",
          "audio": "audio/vos.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "illes",
          "roman": "illes",
          "english": "they",
          "ipa": "ˈiles",
          "audio": "audio/illes.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "ha",
          "roman": "ha",
          "english": "has / have",
          "note": "Same trick: io ha, tu ha, nos ha.",
          "ipa": "hˈa",
          "audio": "audio/ha.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Nos ha un can.",
          "roman": "nos ha un can",
          "english": "We have a dog.",
          "ipa": "nˈos ha un kˈan",
          "audio": "audio/nos-ha-un-can.wav"
        }
      ],
      "exercises": [
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "prompt": "\"Illes ha un can\" means…",
          "choices": [
            "They have a dog",
            "We have a cat",
            "He has a dog",
            "You have a dog"
          ],
          "answer": 0,
          "tts": "illes ha un can"
        },
        {
          "type": "type",
          "prompt": "Translate: \"we have\"",
          "answer": "nos ha",
          "tts": "nos ha"
        },
        {
          "type": "listen",
          "ttsText": "vos",
          "prompt": "Which pronoun did you hear?",
          "choices": [
            "vos",
            "nos",
            "illes"
          ],
          "answer": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "prompt": "Fill the blank: \"Nos ___ felice.\"",
          "choices": [
            "es",
            "ha",
            "io",
            "tu"
          ],
          "answer": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "match",
          "prompt": "Match the pronouns",
          "pairs": [
            [
              "nos",
              "we"
            ],
            [
              "vos",
              "you (pl.)"
            ],
            [
              "illes",
              "they"
            ],
            [
              "ha",
              "have"
            ]
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
